# Plan Filename Date Prefix

When creating a plan file in `.cursor/plans/`, prefix the filename with the current date in `%y%m%d_` (YYMMDD_) format.
IF plan was built, it should be saved to built plans folder. If plan was not built, and left unbuilt, move to archived plan folder.

## Pattern

```
.cursor/plans/<YYMMDD>_<original-plan-name>.plan.md
```

## Examples

```
# ❌ BAD
.cursor/plans/autopilot_http_debug_logging_c4c87156.plan.md

# ✅ GOOD (for 2026-05-11)
.cursor/plans/260511_autopilot_http_debug_logging_c4c87156.plan.md
```

Use the actual current date (e.g. `260604` for 2026-06-04). Keep the rest of the original plan name unchanged.
